cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Protocol Implementation Interoperability Dataset
abstract: This dataset contains experimental results from testing multiple QUIC protocol
  implementations across two networked Linux nodes (tartu and tallinn). The methodology
  involved client-server interactions configured with various parameters to assess
  performance. Execution time, energy consumption, and data synchronization success
  were measured during the tests. Evaluation compared client and server hash values
  for consistency, analyzed process timing, and computed goodput metrics from JSON
  results files.
